thread.title_full: College football week 6 rewind - Houston Chronicle

author: chron.com
title: College football week 6 rewind
text:
Twenty years ago the Southwest Conference played its final season of football primarily because four of its eight members believed they needed to be part of a league with more national appeal. Back in 1995, they'd be surprised at the Associated Press poll midway through the 2015 season.
Baylor, which moved on to the Big 12 with Texas, Texas A&M and Texas Tech, is ranked second.
TCU, left behind at the time (but joining the Big 12 in 2012 in the absence of A&M), is ranked third.
And Houston, another program that had to seek out a new conference following the SWC's disbanding, cruised into the polls at No. 24 on Sunday.
The Cougars, under first-year coach Tom Herman, are ranked for the first time since the end of the 2011 season under then-coach Kevin Sumlin. UT and Tech aren't ranked, and Sumlin-led A&M, which bolted the Big 12 for the Southeastern Conference in 2012, is ninth for a second consecutive week.
Even if the old SWC failed to live on, some of its original castoffs certainly have.
Check out the gallery to see the highs, lows, Quote: of the week and Heisman watch for week six of college football action.
